f=Cybersecurity/keyring/custom/identity-lifecycle/SKILL.md · in=disciplined management *human* identity across life, built **Hack23 access-control-policy** framework policy layer (RBAC, zero-trust, MFA, ISO 27001-aligned access control matrix) custom operational JML workflow execution layer (joiner/mover/leaver step-by-step). joiner gets exactly access their role needs, mover's old access removed new added, **leaver fully deprovisioned promptly.** keyring designs recommends this; operator (or IdP) executes grant/revoke keyring holds keys (the security-inversion). **Policy framework sourced from:** Hack23 access-control-policy (ISO 27001 A.5.15, A.8.2, A.8.3 aligned). access control matrix (6-tier asset classification MFA method, session timeout, review frequency), zero-trust architecture, dormant account detection come Hack23 skill, unaltered. JML operational workflow below custom. · p=single loudest identity gap breach report **departed employee (or contractor) live access** accounts never deprovisioned, becoming unmonitored way in. JML discipline closes it, keeps least-privilege true people change roles rather accumulating access forever (privilege creep). · wu=Someone joins, changes role, leaves (the JML events)., "Provision access X," "did deprovision Y," "why still access.", Periodic reconciliation (accounts actual people orphan detection)., Referencing Hack23 access control matrix MFA requirements, session timeouts, review cadences asset classification. · st:/ Protocol=`POLICY LAYER (Hack23 access-control-policy — unaltered reference) \· Asset classification → RBAC model → MFA requirements → zero-trust architecture \· ↓ feeds into \· JML WORKFLOW (custom — this skill) \· JOINER (role → least-privilege access set; granted by operator/IdP)` · h3:Phase Policy Reference (Hack23)=**Reference Hack23 access control matrix.** Hack23 skill defines asset categories (RESTRICTED High High Moderate Low Public) corresponding MFA requirements, session timeouts (1hr days), re